WEBVTT


00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.400
Earth's ideal conditions for life

00:00:02.400 --> 00:00:05.060
stem from its optimal position in the cosmos,

00:00:05.120 --> 00:00:08.180
offering liquid water and Protection from meteorites.

00:00:08.640 --> 00:00:10.000
The magnetic field

00:00:10.000 --> 00:00:12.420
shaped by molten material in the core

00:00:12.440 --> 00:00:14.460
Shields against space particles

00:00:14.480 --> 00:00:17.900
as revealed by ancient rocks through paleomagnetism.

00:00:18.240 --> 00:00:20.540
Fluctuations in the field's intensity

00:00:20.800 --> 00:00:23.380
influenced by the outer cores turbulent flow

00:00:23.480 --> 00:00:26.220
lead to unpredictable polarity reversals.

00:00:26.680 --> 00:00:28.400
During low intensity phases,

00:00:28.400 --> 00:00:30.840
earth faces increased exposure to solar

00:00:30.840 --> 00:00:34.260
wind and cosmic rays impacting the atmosphere.

00:00:34.560 --> 00:00:37.660
While no direct link to mass extinctions is certain,

00:00:37.760 --> 00:00:39.420
uncertainties persist,

00:00:39.600 --> 00:00:42.000
imposing risks to human civilization

00:00:42.000 --> 00:00:45.260
during periods of reduced geomagnetic intensity.

00:00:45.760 --> 00:00:48.020
The sporadic nature of these changes

00:00:48.080 --> 00:00:50.700
emphasizes the need for preparedness.
